Rating: 4
This is a seriously WONDERFUL recipe! I had a 2 lb. boneless pork rib roast and it worked perfectly. Following what others have said, I cut back on the salt used to season the pork roast, and I used homemade chicken stock (only 1 cup's worth instead of the original recipe's 1-1/2 cups), but kept the remaining ingredients pretty much the same. Instead of melting the butter and adding the flour to make a roux, I made a modified beurre manié with 2 Tbsp. of butter and 1-1/2 flour. I didn't have fresh sage or savory, but used 1/2 tsp. dried savory and a healthy pinch of dried sage in the olive oil/mustard/shallots/garlic mixture and it was just fine. Fresh thyme and rosemary sprigs underneath the roast and on top of the mustard blend really adds a nice flavor - top notch recipe!

